channel.title: Client sided compiler error [PI]
channel.description:
I just registered my server and must log into the account mopar gave me, i have the files read only if that makes a difference, but my compiler says [code]Node.java: error while writing Node: Node.class <access is denied> Public class Node { ^ 1 error
[code] please help :D[/code]

I just registered my server and must log into the account mopar gave me, i have the files read only if that makes a difference, but my compiler says

[code]Node.java: error while writing Node: Node.class
Public class Node {
^
1 error

please help :D

public should not be capitalized.
[/quote]
I think its that the .class files can not be read-only[/quote]

No its that the ‘public’ is capitalized, the JVM is very specific and if you use wrong syntax it will let you know.
